				<div class="description">
					<p>
						This program gets a link and continually goes to that link depending on the time specified. For instance, if you put 10 seconds, then it will keep "pinging" your website every 10 seconds. The purpose of the program is to keep sending requests to the site to keep it awake. If you have a free hosting site such is the case with Heroku, then they will put your site to sleep if there is no activity. With this PingBot, your site will continue to stay awake. Servers will not be able to shut your site down if there is a constant stream of requests coming in.
						<br>
						I would put an example of it on here, but I used bootstrap to make it instead of Semantic-UI. I did not want to have two frameworks on one site. Please feel free to look at the source code and copy it yourself.  
					</p>
